column5: We have a group heading to Carling Lake through Winoga Lodge the week of July 6th. Any tips and advice would be greatly appreciated. We've used Winoga many times, but this is the first time on Carling. Appreciate any info provided.

No advise, but I did a quick tour of that cabin while up there on another mission 3 years ago, it was a nice cabin. There is one other outfitter cabin on Carling. There are lake trout in the lake besides walleye, so it might be fun for you to catch a few of those. All of the lakes in that area are good fishing, you will have a great time.
Appreciate the info. Definitely excited to try fishing for Lake Trout.
